title: '"Protectors fear one another, which keeps them in extreme positions. Each part believes that relaxing will allow a polarized part to take over, with catastrophic consequences. Therefore in IFS we continually notice and attend to polarizations. Just like family therapists, we work with conflicted inner family members, inviting them to face each other and talk about how they can get along better. The difference is that, whenever possible, the client’s Self moderates these inner dialogues, aiming to ensure that parts are respectful and able to listen to each other."'
pid: 49afe3f3-5ba3-4cad-a569-6e25037e76ca
